Rating: 4
This is a delicious soup! I could eat the whole batch - like a liquid salad, perfect for summer. My tweaks: yellow onion; less oil, homemade chicken broth; white wine vinegar; cilantro not parsley; no Worcestershire; 1 L. tomato juice, added hot chili pepper, 4 cloves garlic, dash cumin, garnished with mint leaves. My comments: 1-this is NOT a labor-intensive recipe, as some reviews suggest. It is chopping veggies, just like making a salad. By the time my egg was boiled, I had the veggies chopped. Don't worry about making them the same size/shape/whatever. Also, if you are measuring your chopped veggies to the exact amount specified, you have too much time on your hands - just grab 4-5 tomatoes, a couple cuces, a small pepper, half an onion, etc. I didn't measure ANYthing, including the liquid components. Tasting along the way saves having to wash all those measuring cups! 2-It helps to have a garlic press, makes it super easy to mash the egg/garlic/salt together. 3-I can't imagine using anything but 100% tomato juice, as the whole point is to let the natural flavor of the veggies shine through. 4-Do not even think about skipping the 4+ hours in the fridge. The point here is not to make it cold, but to let all the flavors meld and develop - something that simply chilling the tomato juice cannot do. Plus, it really thickens up nicely after time in the fridge.

