Absolutely fantastic - the very best Gazpacho ever!!! Made it exactly as written 2 weeks ago to rave reviews. Made it again first thing this morning with some revisions which I think make it even more delicious. Revisions: increased amounts of tomatoes, green pepper and cucumber; decreased olive oil to 1/4 cup; added juice and finely grated zest of 1 lemon and 1 lime; added 1/2 cup fresh minced cilantro. In the blender I pureed the Worcestershire, 4 cloves garlic, 2 large jalapenos, and the hard-boiled egg until smooth, then added to the veggie mix. I pureed about 1/3 of the resulting veggie mixture, then returned it to the pot, and added 3 cups extra spicy V8 and 3 cups extra spicy Clamato juice. Finally, I added sea salt and lots of course ground pepper, several dashes of Tabasco, and countered the acidity of all the tomatoes with 2 tsp. sugar. Otherwise, I followed the recipe. With these changes, this Gazpacho is nothing short of sublime! Used all fresh herbs from my garden and I think that made a big difference. Last weekend I was at a very elegant, black tie, gourmet dinner and ball (10 course meal with 7 different wines!)and a very refreshing Gazpacho Sorbet was served as one of the appetizer courses - simply wonderful! So, I am going to give it a try and puree, then freeze the leftover Gazpacho so it is like a savory sorbet or granita. As written, this recipe is truly great; with the changes I made, I think it is truly incredible! Please give it a try - you will not be disappointed!

